Another AI moral story to excuse a sensational action or survival flick.

Thanks to extremezone for always being awesome.

The movie itself? Horrible. The cast and crew seemed to have had their hearts into it, but the film is really just a good example of how too little money and too little talent just can't serve a concept like this with any competence. They did what they could as well as they could. An A for effort for an F for the final result.
Very good quality, very bad movie, iRobot wannabe, total fail....lowbudget
